column5: also, change the batteries in your smoke detectors.
Thanks... i dint even realize it... only clocks I had with me were on my cell phone... and we woke up late anyways....  lol  just changed all the clocks i nthe house.. and one battery
NO! I missed Mercer at 9am cause I woke up at 9:30 in stead of 8:30...i wasn't too impressed haha
Totally caught me off guard, I was going to have breakfast but then I realized it should be lunch!!  Don`t worry Mike Dave will forgive you ONCE but don`t let it happen again!!
Getting up this morning felt wrong.  JF
Was nice to not wake up at 5 in order to make first light.....  About the only thing good about it.
Too bad this board doesn't have the time change worked out.  Yes, I have DST checked in my controls; yes, I have reloaded the board index, but the time is wrong. I have real issues with time.
Still rolled out of bed when I felt like it.. and left work when I felt like it. Nothing changed!  Time is correct on mine Rob...
Everything but the biological clock (and OFC), sprang forward

it's right on OFC here  for a few moments today I thought I had time traveled, but it turned out the one place I was at didn't change there clocks ahead, so I arrived at the next stop half an hour before I left that place .......

Somehow I thought being the boss would work like that for me. The mistake I made was asking my wife to help us out with the new business startup. Guess I'm not the boss after all. At least when I get out of town on my other job I can pretend.  JF
Yup...it was great my 12hr night shift was turned into and 11hr night shift....but I did 2hrs of overtime so really it evened out lol
Really messed me up, I never got outta bed till nearly 4:00 A.M.  I HATE getting up when the day is 1/2 over

Musta been really traumatic. It's even got you repeating yerself.  JF
im in scarborough and mine is set to eastern time and it is behind it is now 8:40 and the comp 7:40
The attendance at church was a little light.I slept thru it also. Joe
